{{Quote|O Tree, our Father, old as moons, / Listen to our plea./Lead our spirits when we meet / Our deadly enemy.|Logray|<ref name="The Adventures of Teebo: A Tale of Magic and Suspense">''[[The Adventures of Teebo: A Tale of Magic and Suspense]]''</ref>}}
The '''Father Tree''' was the tallest tree on the forest [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of [[Endor/Legends|Endor]] and was worshiped as a [[Deity/Legends|deity]] by the [[Ewok/Legends|Ewoks]]. The tree was protected by the [[Grudakk]], a large creature who lived in a burrow under its roots. [[Logray/Legends|Logray]], [[Shaman/Legends|shaman]] of [[Bright Tree Village/Legends|Bright Tree Village]], possessed a branch from the Father Tree that he used to call upon the spirit of the Father Tree.

